1
00:00:06,465 --> 00:00:09,635
<i>["Day You Laugh"</i>
<i>by Toyonaga Toshiyuki]</i>

2
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:16,642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

3
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:23,982
<i>[man singing in Japanese]</i>

4
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:31,031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

5
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:53,220
‐ ♪ Da da da da! ♪
Banzai!

6
00:00:53,220 --> 00:00:54,554
[men shouting]

7
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:56,640
‐ See, Dotachin's more than
a friend to us.

8
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,684
He's also our brakeman.

9
00:00:58,684 --> 00:01:01,603
‐ Anyway, this is good.
I'm glad Shizuo got arrested

10
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:02,938
after he quit.

11
00:01:02,938 --> 00:01:04,189
Can't have any bad apples.

12
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:05,816
‐ Raa‐‐uhh!

13
00:01:05,816 --> 00:01:09,027
AKABAYASHI: I think a nap would
do you a world of good.

14
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:11,905
Hey, mind if I join the party?

15
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:15,033
<i>[man singing in Japanese]</i>

16
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:21,206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,038
SHIKI: Whether by fate
or by accident,

18
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:02,581
one thing's for sure:

19
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:05,584
people can't help
meeting each other.

20
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:08,045
They meet and part ways
as friends

21
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:11,465
just to pass each other
later on and come into conflict.

22
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:13,759
Who knows why that is.

23
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:15,927
‐ Why don't you call it a day,
Anri?

24
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:18,764
I'm gonna go home
and take a shower myself.

25
00:02:18,764 --> 00:02:20,557
When he wakes up,
I'll tell him, "Yo,

26
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,268
"if you came to sooner,
you would have seen this angel

27
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:27,189
in a sexy maid outfit with
glasses and a huge rack," okay?

28
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:28,273
‐ Okay.

29
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:31,276
<i>[somber music]</i>

30
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:33,028
I feel bad calling her,

31
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:36,156
but I need to talk to someone.

32
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:39,201
[line ringing]

33
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:40,952
WOMAN: The person
you're trying to reach

34
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:43,622
is either out of our
service area or is not‐‐

35
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:46,667
<i>[somber music continues]</i>

36
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:50,754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:53,715
‐ Hey, there, Maju.
How's my niece doing?

38
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,592
‐ Hmm? Hey, what's up?

39
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:58,345
‐ Can you believe that shit?
Hit and run on my turf.

40
00:02:58,345 --> 00:02:59,846
Can't wait to catch him.

41
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,641
‐ It's lucky the guy
that got hit didn't die.

42
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:04,851
Things are gonna start
getting crazy here.

43
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,937
‐ Yeah. I heard
the victim's supposed to be

44
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:08,480
a big shot in a gang.

45
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:11,358
‐ Yep. Kyohei Kadota
of the Dollars.

46
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:14,820
The town's also buzzing about
Shizuo Heiwajima's arrest.

47
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:16,655
Everyone in Public Safety's
gonna be slammed

48
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:18,365
till it calms down.

49
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:20,283
‐ Shizuo Heiwajima.

50
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:22,369
Is he the guy
who dresses like a bartender?

51
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:24,830
‐ Yep, that's him‐‐they say
he's involved in the Dollars

52
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:27,833
and that he's friends with that
Headless Rider thing too.

53
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,502
‐ No way!
Him and that monster are tight?

54
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:32,337
Ha. The last thing I expected

55
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:34,548
was for it
to have a social life.

56
00:03:35,674 --> 00:03:37,509
‐ Come on,
don't be so pissed off.

57
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:39,511
He'll be out in no time.
You'll see.

58
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:41,763
‐ I do not understand
invocation here.

59
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:43,890
What reason would I have
to be angry

60
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,725
because Shizuo
have been arrested?

61
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:48,019
There is no connection
between two things.

62
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:50,063
‐ Well, at least you knew
what "pissed off" meant.

63
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,565
I'll give ya that.

64
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,693
‐ I do not understand
why Shizuo have been arrested.

65
00:03:54,693 --> 00:03:56,820
This make no sense at all.

66
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,738
‐ The cops always
had their eye on him.

67
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,532
All they needed
was an excuse to jump.

68
00:04:00,532 --> 00:04:02,367
So when that chick
filed that complaint,

69
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,453
they saw their chance, see?

70
00:04:04,453 --> 00:04:06,246
We both know
Shizuo's not the type of guy

71
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:07,998
to kick someone's ass
for no reason,

72
00:04:07,998 --> 00:04:09,458
especially if it's a chick.

73
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,209
It's either
a big misunderstanding

74
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:14,504
or maybe‐‐I don't know‐‐
someone's trying to frame him.

75
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:18,550
‐ If you just wanna
question him,

76
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:20,135
why does he have to go in?

77
00:04:20,135 --> 00:04:21,928
I'm callin' my lawyer!
‐ Don't worry, boss.

78
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:24,556
I haven't done anything wrong,
so it's cool.

79
00:04:24,556 --> 00:04:27,225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

80
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:31,730
‐ To break out of cell would be
like play of child for Shizuo.

81
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:34,649
Then if he is fugitive from law
I can fight him

82
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:37,402
and claim
I was defending self later.

83
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:41,114
But then, cannot pay him back
for coffee in can

84
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:44,785
or for taking me
to delicious cake shop.

85
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:47,204
And there is also fact
I am not yet skilled enough

86
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:48,747
to defeat him.

87
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:50,916
But why do I do this?

88
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:55,545
Why do I keep looking for reason
to <i>not</i> fight Shizuo?

89
00:04:57,088 --> 00:05:00,675
‐ Is long time no see,
da, Varona?

90
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:02,344
‐ Sloan‐‐is you!

91
00:05:02,344 --> 00:05:03,887
[gasps]

92
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:05,931
So you survive after all.

93
00:05:05,931 --> 00:05:08,600
Why have you not contacted me
until now?

94
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:12,187
‐ I would have liked to,
but I've been a little busy.

95
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:15,899
[muffled] They ripped out
ten of my teeth.

96
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:19,236
And now the Awakusu
assigned me new job

97
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:22,364
as assistant to broker
of information in city.

98
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:24,950
‐ I am sorry,
but I am also relieved

99
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,409
that you are still living.

100
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:28,787
‐ No time for relief.
Keep guard up.

101
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:33,250
If you know what good,
you will get out of city.

102
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:36,127
Soon it will become dangerous
here for you.

103
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:38,129
‐ You make no sense.
Only danger here

104
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:40,215
is becoming bored with self.

105
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:41,508
‐ War is to happen here,

106
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:44,219
and you and I are to be used
as pawns in it.

107
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:45,637
‐ I welcome challenge.

108
00:05:45,637 --> 00:05:48,306
If anyone should dare
to drag me into plot,

109
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:51,977
I am more than able
to make them regret decision.

110
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:54,312
‐ But how can you be sure
you will fight as before?

111
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:57,649
Life in peace of city does
nothing but dull edge, da?

112
00:05:57,649 --> 00:06:00,610
‐ How dare you question
my skill as fighter.

113
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,946
Are you mocking me?
‐ Now, now, Sloan.

114
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:05,156
You shouldn't be so mean
to the lady.

115
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:08,493
Sometimes peace and quiet
is what a body needs.

116
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:11,621
Perhaps the tranquility
of the city has recharged her

117
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,623
and now she's become
even more dangerous

118
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:15,542
than she ever was before.

119
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:17,419
‐ And...you are?

120
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:19,546
‐ That's right.
We never officially met.

121
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:21,298
I hired you before, though.

122
00:06:21,298 --> 00:06:25,343
I'm Izaya Orihara, the info
broker of this wonder city.

123
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:27,429
‐ Izaya Orihara.

124
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:29,097
Da. I remember.

125
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:32,017
‐ Really? I hire you for one
job, and you remember me?

126
00:06:32,017 --> 00:06:33,852
[chuckles]
You are a‐‐

127
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:35,061
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

128
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:36,354
[grunting]

129
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:38,356
‐ I have heard rumor
from others on street

130
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:40,567
you are mortal enemy of Shizuo.

131
00:06:40,567 --> 00:06:43,153
I will now take opportunity
to annihilate you

132
00:06:43,153 --> 00:06:46,323
and return multitude favors
I am owing him.

133
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:49,367
‐ Well...I didn't know Shizuo
had the charm

134
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:50,702
to tame a girl like you.

135
00:06:50,702 --> 00:06:52,162
[exhales] Whatever.

136
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,956
It should be amusing to see
whose pawn you become.

137
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:57,542
And since observing humans
is a hobby of mine,

138
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,252
you've piqued my interest.

139
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:02,339
I am looking forward to watching
what happens to you next.

140
00:07:02,339 --> 00:07:04,966
Even if you're friends
with a monster like him,

141
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,926
I still like you as a human.

142
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:11,598
Apparently,
the feeling is not mutual.

143
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:12,974
Back to work.

144
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:14,476
‐ Hmm? What do you mean?

145
00:07:14,476 --> 00:07:16,227
I thought we are done for day.

146
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:20,065
‐ Not quite. I haven't heard
from Namie since it got dark.

147
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:23,193
I think it's safe to say
they got to her first.

148
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:25,487
We have to wrap this up
by tomorrow morning.

149
00:07:25,487 --> 00:07:28,365
The sooner we do, the better for
your ex‐comrade here.

150
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:32,577
With any luck, she can avoid
becoming their pawn.

151
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:34,287
SHIKI: Izaya Orihara's taunts

152
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,956
filled Varona's heart
with cold poison,

153
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,708
‐ [Izaya chuckles]
SHIKI: Changing it back into

154
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,170
the icy thing it was when she
first arrived in the city.

155
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,757
AKABAYASHI:
You got a problem I'm here,

156
00:07:45,757 --> 00:07:47,759
Mikado?
‐ Huh?

157
00:07:52,347 --> 00:07:54,349
[whimpers]

158
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:59,396
Crap! He's gonna kill me.

159
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:01,981
I don't wanna die.

160
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:05,151
Not yet‐‐I still have
so much to do.

161
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:06,528
Oh, God!

162
00:08:06,528 --> 00:08:09,406
‐ Ha. Ya passed the test, kid.

163
00:08:09,406 --> 00:08:13,118
A real gangster ain't gonna
shit himself in a staredown.

164
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:15,036
‐ Huh?
‐ You got a problem, old man?

165
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:18,248
‐ What's up, bitch?
You got a death wish?

166
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,668
‐ Uhh‐‐ugh!

167
00:08:23,712 --> 00:08:25,588
‐ How'd you do that?

168
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:28,383
‐ I picked up a few tricks
in my day.

169
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:31,636
Hell, some folks think
I'm psychic, I move so fast.

170
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,346
[chuckling]
Can you beat that?

171
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:36,433
What do you think, Transporter?
Am I psychic?

172
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,810
‐ Sorry.
Who are you?

173
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,353
CELTY:
Is it okay to tell him?

174
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:44,023
‐ Sure, go ahead.
It's what I came here to do.

175
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:47,694
‐ This is Mr. Akabayashi.
He's with the Awakusus.

176
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:49,571
‐ The Awakusus?

177
00:08:49,571 --> 00:08:51,197
‐ Hey, you heard of us!

178
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,866
Then I guess
I don't have to tell you

179
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:55,452
if a guy like me
comes around looking for ya,

180
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:56,995
it's gotta be serious.

181
00:08:56,995 --> 00:09:00,206
‐ Is it us?
Have we caused you trouble?

182
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:03,626
‐ Well... let's just say
you have our attention.

183
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:06,796
Some of the higher‐ups think
we need to take action.

184
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,840
But I'm not into
roughing up civvies.

185
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,467
Kind of a rule with me.

186
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:11,968
‐ Ohh...

187
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,012
‐ I'm here
to give you a choice.

188
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:16,556
You can either be our partners
or get stomped.

189
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:18,099
Take your pick.

190
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:20,518
<i>[slow jazzy music]</i>

191
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:22,479
‐ If the Dollars
did your group wrong,

192
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:25,065
I swear we didn't mean it.
It's just...

193
00:09:25,065 --> 00:09:27,358
all we want
is a place to belong.

194
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:29,069
‐ Oh. Is that all?

195
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:31,404
I'm sure there's tons of places
like that

196
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:33,198
on the right side of the law.

197
00:09:33,198 --> 00:09:34,491
‐ Mm.

198
00:09:34,491 --> 00:09:37,911
‐ Consider this your first
and last warning.

199
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,996
I don't wanna give you
a hard time.

200
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:42,373
Just letting you know
that folks like me

201
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:44,042
got ya on the radar now.

202
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:46,669
‐ I appreciate you
doing that for us.

203
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:49,547
‐ Mm‐hmm. You got manners, kid.
I like that.

204
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:52,884
Now I'm gonna leave you
with some advice.

205
00:09:52,884 --> 00:09:55,386
Quit the Dollars now,
and you'll be better off for it.

206
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:58,932
If your parents find out
you're the leader of a gang,

207
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:00,725
it'll break their hearts.

208
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,686
This kinda life ain't good
for you or your friends,

209
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,772
especially that girl
you're tight with‐‐

210
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,899
you know,
the one with the glasses.

211
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:09,901
‐ Anri's got nothing
to do with this!

212
00:10:09,901 --> 00:10:11,736
‐ See, that's what
I'm talkin' about, kid.

213
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:14,322
You just let me know
how important she is to you.

214
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:16,157
Now I'll tell you
something about me.

215
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:19,619
For six months now, I've been
a member of the Dollars.

216
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:21,746
‐ [gasps]
‐ Crazy, huh?

217
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:23,665
Just so you know,
I'll be talking about you later

218
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:25,250
with the rider here.

219
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:29,212
‐ Any time. And for the record,
Mikado's not stupid.

220
00:10:29,212 --> 00:10:30,713
He won't get on your bad side.

221
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,799
AKABAYASHI: I hope you're right.

222
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:35,969
CELTY: I know I am.

223
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:38,096
‐ Well, before I go,
I need a favor

224
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:39,889
for something Dollar‐related.

225
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:42,308
Seeing as how I'm a Dollar too,
I'd like to ask you

226
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:44,477
to help a friend of mine
who's in a jam.

227
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:47,063
‐ Who?
‐ You're up, Niekawa.

228
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:49,274
Come on out
and meet the boss man.

229
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:51,276
CELTY: Niekawa?

230
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:56,114
‐ Thanks.
I‐‐Uh‐‐

231
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:58,116
The shy‐looking kid's
the leader?

232
00:10:58,116 --> 00:10:59,868
For real?
‐ Yep. He's about

233
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:02,036
the closest thing
to a leader the Dollars have.

234
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:05,373
Sure, he might not look it,
but I think he can help you.

235
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:08,168
‐ You're Niekawa, the writer
with the "Tokyo Warriors."

236
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:09,460
‐ Yeah, that's‐‐
[gasps]

237
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:10,962
It's‐‐it's the Headless Rider!

238
00:11:10,962 --> 00:11:12,213
‐ What are <i>you</i> doing here?

239
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:14,090
Are you friends
with Mr. Akabayashi?

240
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,551
‐ No, n‐not exactly.
Like he said,

241
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:18,887
I'm here to get help.
‐ Um... Celty?

242
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:20,805
Is this guy a friend
