00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:10,478
I bet you killed the real
Kujiragi and stole her identity.

488
00:21:10,478 --> 00:21:12,563
KUJIRAGI:
I didn't steal anything.

489
00:21:12,563 --> 00:21:14,565
It was a mutual transaction.

490
00:21:14,565 --> 00:21:17,151
‐ Well, either way,
I don't know your real name,

491
00:21:17,151 --> 00:21:19,361
and that just won't do.

492
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:21,280
I tried to expose
everything around you,

493
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:24,200
and that's why those poor
old decoys had to go.

494
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,826
I hope you understand.

495
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:28,662
On a different topic,
you hijacked my Kanra chat name,

496
00:21:28,662 --> 00:21:30,080
didn't you?

497
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:33,209
Was ending your post with "meow"
your way of taunting me?

498
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:35,669
KUJIRAGI: I thought it was cute.
‐ [sighs]

499
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:38,422
Right. So are you going to
tell me where Namie is?

500
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:39,924
She's a proud woman,

501
00:21:39,924 --> 00:21:42,092
but unfortunately,
she hates my guts.

502
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,761
When she finds out I saved her,

503
00:21:43,761 --> 00:21:45,930
the look on her face
will be epic.

504
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:48,474
‐ That doesn't sound
very honorable.

505
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:50,267
‐ Well, that's funny,
coming from a woman

506
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:52,436
who does everything
from human trafficking

507
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,104
to monster trafficking.

508
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:55,606
Know what I find ironic?

509
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:58,567
Saika‐‐the blade you sold
to Shingen Kishitani.

510
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:01,111
It's being used against you now.
Thoughts?

511
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:04,031
KUJIRAGI: There's a reason why
I let something so valuable

512
00:22:04,031 --> 00:22:05,449
go so easily.

513
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:08,452
Besides slashing humans
to create new offspring,

514
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:11,539
Saika has another way
to expand her reach.

515
00:22:11,539 --> 00:22:14,208
I like to call it replication.
‐ Huh?

516
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:17,837
‐ Simply put,
if you break Saika's blade,

517
00:22:17,837 --> 00:22:20,381
you can make new swords
from the pieces.

518
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:27,680
[thudding, clatter over phone]

519
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,640
<i>[dark string music]</i>

520
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:32,101
SLOAN: Mother,
I have captured Izaya.

521
00:22:32,101 --> 00:22:34,687
‐ Would you please bring him
to number 12's office?

522
00:22:34,687 --> 00:22:36,188
I'd like to ask him
some questions

523
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:39,275
about the Dullahan's head.
‐ Da, Mother.

524
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:43,779
‐ Thank you very much,
Mr. Izaya Orihara.

525
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:46,991
You destroyed the group
called Jinnai Yodogiri.

526
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:49,618
I'll be forever grateful
for that.

527
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:52,621
<i>[eerie music]</i>

528
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:54,915
Thank you for my freedom.

529
00:22:54,915 --> 00:22:57,751
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

530
00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:59,837
CELTY: I've been alive
for centuries,

531
00:22:59,837 --> 00:23:03,007
and I can't even talk sense
into one boy.

532
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:04,466
‐ Oh, Celty, you're home!

533
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:06,552
We were getting worried
about you.

534
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:09,013
‐ Hi, Emilia.
I had a tough day and‐‐

535
00:23:09,013 --> 00:23:10,890
What's with all the food?

536
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:13,017
‐ We're having ourselves
a dinner party tonight!

537
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:15,561
And we're gonna have tons of fun
with tons of yummy food

538
00:23:15,561 --> 00:23:19,440
and tons of yummy people
and more food!

539
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:22,234
Guess who's in time
for din‐dins!

540
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:25,321
<i>[eerie music continues]</i>

541
00:23:25,321 --> 00:23:27,114
<i>♪ ♪</i>

542
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:29,700
Now, this is what I call...
‐ It's nice to meet you.

543
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,243
‐ Who the‐‐
[engine whirs]

544
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:34,496
‐ Welcome home, Celty.
I missed you so much today.

545
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:36,206
You'd think having all these
people hanging out

546
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:38,042
would help kill the loneliness,
but they don't.

547
00:23:38,042 --> 00:23:39,627
You're the only one
who can do that.

548
00:23:39,627 --> 00:23:42,379
‐ Thank you, you're sweet.
What's going on?

549
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:44,381
Why is everyone
in our apartment?

550
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:46,300
‐ Yeah, funny story...

551
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:48,469
SHIKI: Whether by fate
or by design,

552
00:23:48,469 --> 00:23:50,763
these people
were brought together here

553
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:53,891
in this... apartment.

554
00:23:56,727 --> 00:23:59,730
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

555
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:06,737
<i>♪ ♪</i>

